{"parse":{"title":"The Leiden school","pageid":3064983,"revid":811382035,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>The Leiden school</b> is a school of thought in <a href=\"/wiki/Linguistics\" title=\"Linguistics\">linguistics</a> that models languages as <a href=\"/wiki/Meme\" title=\"Meme\">memes</a> or benign neurological parasites,<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and tries to use rigorous mathematical tools borrowed by analogy from biological evolution to model the origin and spread of language in general and specific languages in particular.\n</p><p>It is based at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Leiden\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"University of Leiden\">University of Leiden</a>, and its chief proponents are <a href=\"/wiki/George_van_Driem\" title=\"George van Driem\">George van Driem</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Frederik_Kortlandt\" title=\"Frederik Kortlandt\">Frederik Kortlandt</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/Jeroen_Wiedenhof\" title=\"Jeroen Wiedenhof\">Jeroen Wiedenhof</a>. The Leiden School has a significant overlap in personnel with the <a href=\"/wiki/Himalayan_Languages_Project\" title=\"Himalayan Languages Project\">Himalayan Languages Project</a>.\n</p><p>The Leiden school of linguistics should not be confused with the current research institute of linguistics at Leiden University, the Leiden University Centre for Linguistics (LUCL).\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Leiden_school&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Structural_anthropology\" title=\"Structural anthropology\">Structural anthropology</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Symbiomism\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Symbiomism\">Symbiomism</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Symbiosism\" title=\"Symbiosism\">Symbiosism</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Leiden_school&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://www.semioticon.com/virtuals/imitation/van_driem_paper.pdf\">[1]</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Linguistics_stub.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Linguistics_stub.svg/40px-Linguistics_stub.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"17\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Linguistics_stub.svg/60px-Linguistics_stub.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Linguistics_stub.svg/80px-Linguistics_stub.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"175\" data-file-height=\"74\" /></a></td><td><i>This <a href=\"/wiki/Linguistics\" title=\"Linguistics\">linguistics</a> article is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=The_Leiden_school&amp;action=edit\">expanding it</a>.</i><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\" style=\"position: absolute; right: 15px; display: none;\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Ling-stub\" title=\"Template:Ling-stub\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li c